## 

::: {style="font-size: 2em; color: #000000;"}
How did R calculate the $t$-statistic?
:::

::: panel-tabset
## Step 1: SE

::: columns
::: {.column width="40%"}
$SE_{b_1} = \frac{\frac{s_y}{s_x} \cdot \sqrt{1 - r^2}}{\sqrt{n - 2}}$
:::

::: {.column width="5%"}
:::

::: {.column width="55%"}

::: {.cell}
::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}

```
[1] 0.01495204
```


:::
:::

:::
:::

## Step 2: t-statistic

$t = \frac{b_1}{SE_{b_1}} = \frac{0.067}{0.014952} = 4.4809947$

